M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 and mesotarsomeres 1 and 2 strongly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 97, 98
) 0.94-0.96 mm long, symmetrical, strongly sclerotized. Apical process of median lobe longer than basal bulb, almost evenly narrow in dorsal view, except near apex, inflexed and gradually narrowed in lateral view, with apical section rather abruptly bent. Apex of median lobe acute, articular processes robust and prominent. Parameres slightly extending behind level of apex of median lobe, narrowed toward mid-length, widened in apical third and weakly curved posterior mid-length in dorsal view, almost straight and evenly broad in lateral view. Internal sac simple, without sclerotized parts, with covered dense denticular structures.
